The paper deals with dynamic connectivity, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. The first problem studied is subgraph connectivity, which is relevant to networks of routers and node faults. This suggests the sub-categories cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) as likely candidates. The second problem studied is geometric connectivity, which involves maintaining a dynamic set of geometric objects and querying connectivity in their intersection graph. This suggests the sub-category cs.CG (computational geometry) as another likely candidate. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and improving data structures, which could fall under cs.SI (social and information networks) or cs.DM (discrete mathematics).
